<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880623-0170 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report: Bayer Says Sales Rose 5% In 5 Months, Profit Climbed </HL><SO> </SO><IN> ERN CHM </IN><TEXT>   BAYER AG said group sales rose 5% in the first five months of 1988, and Hermann Strenger, chairman, said the earnings trend from the first quarter, when pretax profit at the West German chemicals giant rose 11% from a year earlier, continued.    Group sales in the five months rose to 16.6 billion marks ($9.46 billion) from 15.8 billion marks a year earlier, and the chairman said he expects sales for the full year to increase slightly from 1987.    Mr. Strenger didn't give precise earnings figures for the five months. He said net income for 1988 will at least match last year's record of 1.54 billion marks. </TEXT></DOC>